long_desc.thetext:
Hello,
It seems that png-images are not being shown in qooxdoo application if a user tries to access the application using Internet Explorer and SSL mode. To see this problem you can put demo browser or api viewer under Apache SSL and try to load that application in IE.
Best regards, Dioc

A colleague of mine found out that this bug is related to IE specific code in qooxdoo that was written to work around transparent PNG problem in IE (see https://blogs.msdn.com/ie/archive/2005/04/26/412263.aspx). It seems that the problem is caused by using DXImageTransform.Microsoft.AlphaImageLoader. For example, qx.ui.basic.Image._updateContent line 546.
Also the colleague of mine found the possible solution for this bug. See http://webfx.eae.net/dhtml/pngbehavior/pngbehavior.html
Denis aka Dioc

We have multiple SSL powered sites without a problem. What exactly should be the problem. The site you mentioned is OK, but there is nothing mentioned regarding SSL. Can you please double-check the error and attach a valid example for testing. Thanks.
Maybe related to #250?
Created attachment 290 Showcase in IE 6 under SSL
Created attachment 291 Demo Browser in IE 6 under SSL

Attached screenshots demonstrate the problem. I use the following servers: - Apache http server 2.0.54 - Apache Tomcat 5.5.23
Denis
Alex, please confirm/fix for 0.7.4
working on this

Fixed this bug in revision #14260 (legacy_0_7_x branch) and #14261 (trunk).
For IE6 it is needed to set a source for any iframe element before it is added to the document. If no source is set the "Unsecure elements" warning is shown. Setting a SSL-aware URL for the source and then adding the iframe to the document solves this issue.
It seems that this problem is not fixed. I can see it in IE 7. But bug #1818 should be fixed to check the problem.
@Denis I've just fixed the issue with #1818. Is this bug still present?
Yes, I can still reproduce this bug by using the latest revision of qooxdoo 0.7.x from svn.
Check latest fix for HTTPS under IE. If the URL is an absolute one using "https://" there should be NO difference to HTTP in the code -> re-check the latest fix concerning this.

In the case that I'm seeing, it looks like the image's Preloader object is returning an improper Uri:
https://<hostname>:7002/https://<hostname>:7002/path/to/image/file.png as opposed to https://<hostname>:7002/path/to/image/file.png

@stoohey The current implementation in legacy_0_7_x branch is to pass through every URL starting with HTTPS. Did you test with the latest revision of the legacy_0_7_x branch or with the latest 0.7.4 release?
Both, actually. I'm really scratching my head on this one.
In Firefox it returns the appropriate value... Apparently IE8 has something very similar to Firebug, so I'm going to try the same thing in IE8 to see what that gives me.

Alright, here's what I've run in IE8's Developer Tools, which is pretty much a direct lift of Firebug:
>>qx.io.Alias.getInstance().resolve("widget/Windows/table/descending.png"); "https://<myhostname>:7002/https://<myhostname>:7002/__/4.10.0.0.000.00/scripts/qooxdoo/resource/qx/widget/Windows/Windows/table/descending.png"
If I run the same thing from Firebug, I get:
"https://<myhostname>:7002/__/4.10.0.0.000.00/scripts/qooxdoo/resource/qx/widget/Windows/Windows/table/descending.png"
Seems the problem is the resolve function on IE...
Any ideas on this one? This seems pretty brutal.

@stoohey Okay, this one seems to be a bit more complicated.
Can you please tell me the value of
--snip-- qx.io.Alias.getInstance()._aliases["widget"] --snip--
so I can dig deeper into this issue?
Thanks a lot, Alex

"http://<hostname>:<port>/__/4.10.0.0.000.00/scripts/qooxdoo/resource/qx/widget/Windows"
Is what I get back. Sorry for the delay in getting back to you, I've since worked around this issue with our own code.
Accepted.
Set to "FIXED"

Thanks, Alex
